# Trivy ignore rules for intentional security constructs
#
# Format: <vuln-id-or-secret-rule> [expiry-date] [# comment]
# Docs: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#trivyignore-file

# ── Canary tokens (Application.kt lines 30-31) ──────────────────────────────
# These are intentional honeypot credentials embedded for exfiltration detection
# (TODO-010 security monitoring). If source code is stolen and credentials used,
# Falco/canarytoken alerts fire. DO NOT treat as real secrets.
aws-access-key-id     # canary token — not a real AWS credential
aws-secret-access-key # canary token — not a real AWS credential
